  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will compare the effect of a new oral agent for type 2 diabetes, sitagliptin, in
      comparison to thiazolidinediones as the third-line oral agent, in patients with type 2
      diabetes mellitus.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this protocol is to determine the non-inferiority of the effectiveness of
      sitagliptin compared to a control group of patients treated with thiazolidinediones as add-on
      therapy, in low-income ethnic minority type 2 diabetic patients who are failing to maintain
      adequate control with maximal doses of metformin and a sulfonylurea agent.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
